main event: An unidentified aerial object was sighted over Iwo Jima on 17 June 1953, reported by a pilot on a return flight from Okinawa Air Base.
interesting points: The object was sighted on radar and a request was made for two Electronics Data Sheets to be completed by personnel involved in the sighting.
Efforts were made to gather all information on the sighting and to identify the source of the radar return.
The Air Technical Intelligence Center established forms to collect information on the sighting and requested completion by the pilot involved.
This report was shared with the Commander of the Far East Air Forces, with coordination dates and names of the personnel involved in the investigation.
The report emphasized the attempt to locate and gather complete information from the pilot involved in the sighting.
result: The sighting remains unexplained, and efforts were made to gather comprehensive information for further investigation.
witnesses: Pilot on a return flight from Okinawa Air Base
photographs: No photographs mentioned in the report
